# plan/facts/09-task-shape-routing-matrix.bn
#
# Task-shape × model-tier routing matrix (M3.12). Pairs canonical task
# shapes with the cost-quality optimum across tiers, drawing on the
# per-model envelope research in facts/08.
#
# Operator reframe 2026-05-03: cheapcode's value is "general-agent that
# routes optimally based on documented failure modes." This file is the
# routing decision-table feeding the auto-tier dispatch logic.
#
# Substrate: mizaj 11 (tier-the-source) for evidence ladder; mizaj 02
# (generate-before-select) — generate the matrix BEFORE picking which
# slice cheapcode commits to in v1.0.
#
# As of 2026-05-03 the matrix is L4-mostly (vendor + leaderboard data).
# Per mizaj 14, claims at L4 cap at 0.40 unless mutawatir-adjusted
# upward by multiple independent sources (which several of these are).

